value.value: A part of a cellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex but below that of an anatomical system. Or, a substance produced by a cellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.
A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Formation of a prolongation or process extending and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: negative regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: positive regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of plasma membrane bounded cell projections.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a plasma membrane bounded prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a cilium or axon.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of a plasma membrane bounded cell projection are generated and organized.
All of the contents of a plasma membrane bounded neuron projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.

label.value: positive regulation of collagen catabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of collagen catabolism. Collagen catabolism is the proteolytic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of collagen in the extracellular matrix.

The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of any steroid hormone, naturally occurring substances secreted by specialized cells that affects the metabolism or behavior of other cells possessing functional receptors for the hormone.

label.value: negative regulation of protein localization to chromatin

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to chromatin.

label.value: positive regulation of protein localization to chromatin

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to chromatin.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of bile acid from a cell or a tissue.

label.value: positive regulation of bile acid secretion

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of bile acid from a cell or a tissue.

label.value: negative regulation of bile acid secretion

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of bile acid from a cell or a tissue.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blastocyst development.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the deposition or modulates the distribution of coloring matter in an organism.
The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of an endothelial tube.
One of the two nuclear divisions that occur as part of the meiotic cell cycle.

A mitotic cell cycle process comprising the steps by which the nucleus of a eukaryotic cell divides; the process involves condensation of chromosomal DNA into a highly compacted form. Canonically, mitosis produces two daughter nuclei whose chromosome complement is identical to that of the mother cell.
The cellular processes that contribute to exocytosis.
The process by which an organelle membrane interacts with another membrane via molecular tethers that physically bridge the two membranes and attach them to each other.

label.value: catalytic activity, acting on a protein

value.value: Catalytic activity that acts to modify a protein.
Catalytic activity that acts to modify DNA.
Catalytic activity that acts to modify RNA, driven by ATP hydrolysis.

label.value: catalytic activity, acting on a glycoprotein

value.value: Catalysis of a biochemical reaction at physiological temperatures in which one of the substrates is a glycoprotein.

The assembly and secretion a set of components to form an extracellular vesicule, a membrane-bounded vesicle that is released into the extracellular region. Extracellular vesicles include exosomes, microvesicles and apoptotic bodies, based on the mechanism by which they are released from cells and differentiated based on their size and content.
Translation that occurs at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: translation at presynapse, modulating chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Translation that occurs at the presynapse, and that modulates chemical synaptic transmission.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Translation that occurs at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Translation that occurs at the postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Any process that regulates translation occurring at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Any process that regulates translation occurring at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Any process that regulates translation occurring at the postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at a synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at a presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at a postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation protein catabolic process at synapse

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation protein catabolic process at presynapse

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation protein catabolic process at postsynapse

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at the postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: A cellular process in which two or more cells combine together, their plasma membrane fusing, producing a single cell. In some cases, nuclei fuse, producing a polyploid cell, while in other cases, nuclei remain separate, producing a syncytium.
Directly binding to a specific protein and delivering it to a specific cellular location.

definition.value: Examples of protein carriers include the soluble TIM chaperone complexes of S. cerevisiae Tim9-Tim10 and Tim8-Tim13, that provide a shuttle system between TOM and the membrane insertases TIM22 and SAM and, thus, ensure that precursors are kept in a translocation-competent conformation.

value.value: The directed movement of some substance from a cell, into the extracellular region. This may occur via transport across the plasma membrane or via exocytosis.
The directed movement of a lipid from a cell, into the extracellular region.
The directed movement of a lipid from outside of a cell into a cell. This may occur via transport across the plasma membrane or via endocytosis.

A stable assembly of two or more macromolecules, i.e. proteins, nucleic acids, carbohydrates or lipids, in which at least one component is a protein and the constituent parts function together in the nucleus.
The division of a vacuole within a cell to form two or more separate vacuoles.

label.value: catalytic activity, acting on a nucleic acid

value.value: Catalytic activity that acts to modify a nucleic acid.
